definition: Ming Dynasty (1368-1644)/surname Ming/Ming (c. 2000 BC), fourth of the legendary Flame Emperors, 炎帝[Yan2 di4] descended from Shennong 神農|神农[Shen2 nong2] Farmer God
bright/opposite: dark 暗[an4]/(of meaning) clear/to understand/next/public or open/wise/generic term for a sacrifice to the gods
not understanding things (idiom); devoid of sense
not to understand the situation/unaware of the ins and outs
although I don't understand it, it seems pretty awesome (Internet slang)
unidentified origin/no-one knows where it comes from/of dubious background

sentences.english: The unidentified armed group used guns to force the Chinese crew to increase speed sailing towards Thailand.
sentences.chinese: 不明武装用枪逼着中国船员加足马力向泰国驶去。

sentences.english: They were never autopsied, and the cause of death remained unknown.
sentences.chinese: 但是并没有进行验尸，死因不明。

sentences.english: The outlook for both markets is uncertain.
sentences.chinese: 这两个市场的前景并不明朗。

sentences.english: This is the most famous, in the history of UFO, the "Roswell Incident".
sentences.chinese: 这就是不明飞行物史上最著名的“罗斯韦尔事件”。

sentences.english: Several women who have suffered the unusual fractures testified at the meeting.
sentences.chinese: 有几位曾患不明原因骨折的女士旁听了这次会议。

sentences.english: I dissent altogether from such an unwise idea.
sentences.chinese: 我对这种不明智的意见全然持异议。

sentences.english: But the demand for the clandestine product would be substantially reduced.
sentences.chinese: 但是，对来历不明的产品的需求将下降。

sentences.english: Some of them are spaceships from outer space.
sentences.chinese: 有些不明飞行物是外太空来访的太空船。

sentences.english: He had earlier claimed to have been shown round a UFO in 2001.
sentences.chinese: 他曾称自己在2001年参观过一个不明飞行物。

sentences.english: But it is still unclear what information was actually peddled.
sentences.chinese: 但是到底兜售什么信息才算内幕交易还仍不明了。

sentences.english: Tepco and the safety agency say the exact source of the leak is unknown.
sentences.chinese: 东京电力和安全机构人士说，泄漏的确切来源不明。

sentences.english: It said the 26-year-old was a parliamentary candidate, citing unidentified sources.
sentences.chinese: 据说26岁的金正云是一个议员，这个消息来源不明。

sentences.english: Aircraft noise is unwitting of passengers.
sentences.chinese: 飞机噪音是旅客不明智所至。

sentences.english: A verdurous snake wreathing in a puddle of unknown green liquid above the ground.
sentences.chinese: 一条碧绿的蛇盘卧在地面上一滩绿色的不明液体中。

sentences.english: Then in wanders the unlucky Sing, who attempts to get money there.
sentences.chinese: 然而不明真相的辛试图从那儿弄到钱。

clear/distinct/to understand thoroughly/to be clear about
